<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She has never been afraid to experiment when it comes to her wardrobe. </p>

<p>And Rita Ora turned heads as she arrived for Fendi's Milan Fashion Week show at the Palazzo della Civiltà Italiana in Rome on Wednesday.</p>

<p>The singer, 29, showcased her incredible physique in a velour black blazer but suffered an awkward mishap as she arrived for the show.  </p>

<p>Rita Ora turned heads as she arrived for Fendi's Milan Fashion Week show at the Palazzo della Civiltà Italiana in Rome on Wednesday.</p>

<p>Rita accidentally flashed her underwear in the thigh-skimming blazer, which had a v cut at the back and dramatic shoulder pads. </p>

<p>The Anywhere hitmaker seemed unperturbed by the fashion faux pas as she strutted into the catwalk show in knee-high fishnets and black heels. </p>

<p>She slicked her blonde hair back into a low bun and amped up the glamour with diamond earrings, a gold phone chain and shades. </p>

